    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="339"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/357</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-11T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.16 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10003. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 560. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WM1">Wallenberg</persName> told
                    me this morning that he thought the Swedish agreement could be concluded next
                    week. Referring to your 409, Department’s 7574 [<hi rend="italic">7564</hi>],
                    May 3. If the British, French, and Italian Governments approve of the terms of
                    the Swedish agreement and are willing to sign it, it is suggested that you
                    authorize me to sign as representative of the War Trade Board a memorandum to
                    the Royal Swedish Government on the following lines: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Referring to the agreement signed this day between the British, French,
                            and Italian Governments on the one hand and the Royal Swedish Government
                            on the other hand, the United States War Trade Board, an administrative
                            agency empowered by Executive order of the President to license exports
                            from the United States, whose powers are administrative and pertain
                            wholly to the United States domestic and internal affairs, agrees to
                            grant licenses during the currency of the above-mentioned agreement for
                            the articles enumerated in the ration list of this agreement in so far
                            as the same (1) are not required for consumption in the United States
                            and in so far as the exportation thereof will not so reduce available
                            supplies as to prevent the rationing of the nations associated with the
                            United States in the war and (2) will not directly or indirectly be
                            exported to any country or ally with which the United States is at war
                            so long as the terms and conditions of the above-mentioned agreement
                            shall be observed by the Royal Swedish Government.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0394" n="1228" xml:id="pg_1228"/>
                <p>Please cable whether you approve or what modifications or suggestions you
                    desire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
